,50,29,128,275,273,785],"class_list":["post-24603","post","type-post","status-publish","format-standard","hentry","category-faith-iman","tag-bad-deeds-al-sayyiat","tag-calamity-al-museebah","tag-forgiveness-al-maghfirah","tag-hardship","tag-humility-al-tawadu","tag-monotheism-tawhid","tag-providence-al-qada-wal-qadr","tag-punishment-al-uqubah","tag-reward-al-ajr","tag-surat-al-rahman"],"aioseo_notices":[],"jetpack_featured_media_url":"","jetpack_shortlink":"https:\/\/wp.me\/p95VHY-6oP","jetpack_sharing_enabled":true,"jetpack-related-posts":[{"id":18509,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2014\/03\/14\/hardship-debt-shade-allah\/","url_meta":{"origin":24603,"position":0},"title":"Hadith on Shade: Helping others in the shade of Allah","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"March 14, 2014","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu al-Yasar reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cWhoever would love to be shaded in the shade of Allah, let him help someone in hardship or waive a loan.\u201d Source: Musnad Ah\u0323mad\u00a015520 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according to Al-Arna\u2019ut \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0623\u064e\u0628\u0650\u064a \u0627\u0644\u0652\u064a\u064e\u0633\u064e\u0631\u0650 \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0631\u064e\u0633\u064f\u0648\u0644\u064f\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":27142,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/02\/05\/believers-not-seek-hardship\/","url_meta":{"origin":24603,"position":1},"title":"Hadith on Trials: Believers do not seek unnecessary hardship","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"February 5, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Hudhayfah reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cIt is not befitting for a believer to humiliate himself.\u201d They said, \u201cHow does he humiliate himself?\u201d The Prophet said, \u201cHe confronts a trial he cannot endure.\u201d Source: Sunan al-Tirmidhi\u0304 2254 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according to Al-Albani\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":33098,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/08\/05\/siwak-miswak-with-every-wudu\/","url_meta":{"origin":24603,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Wudu: Using the toothstick with every ablution","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"August 5, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Ali reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cWere it not hardship for my nation, I would have commanded them to use the toothstick with every ablution.\u201d Source: al-Mu\u2019jam al-Awsat\u0323 1260 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according to Al-Albani \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0639\u064e\u0644\u0650\u064a\u0651\u064d \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0631\u064e\u0633\u064f\u0648\u0644\u064f \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u0650 \u0635\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u064f\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":23969,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2016\/11\/02\/hardship-pain-expiation\/","url_meta":{"origin":24603,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Trials: Every discomfort an expiation for sins","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"November 2, 2016","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Huraira reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cNothing afflicts a Muslim of hardship, nor illness, nor anxiety, nor sorrow, nor harm, nor distress, nor even the pricking of a thorn, but that Allah will expiate his sins by it.\u201d Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 5641, S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/faith-iman\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":35071,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2021\/01\/26\/be-grateful-prosperity\/","url_meta":{"origin":24603,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Adversity: Be grateful in prosperity, Allah helps in hardship","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"January 26, 2021","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Huraira reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cAcknowledge Allah in prosperity, and He will acknowledge you in adversity.\u201d Source: Ama\u0304li\u0304 Ibn Bishra\u0304n 1365 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according to Al-Albani \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0623\u064e\u0628\u0650\u064a \u0647\u064f\u0631\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0631\u064e\u0629\u064e \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0650 \u0627\u0644\u0646\u0651\u064e\u0628\u0650\u064a\u0651\u0650 \u0635\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0647\u0650 \u0648\u064e\u0633\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0645\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u062a\u064e\u0639\u064e\u0631\u0651\u064e\u0641\u0652 \u0625\u0650\u0644\u064e\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u0650 \u0641\u0650\u064a \u0627\u0644\u0631\u0651\u064e\u06